# Raspberri_Pi_Audio (Pi + Behringer UCA202 + OLED)

Local clone: `/home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio`. Python venv: `.venv/` (numpy, sounddevice, luma.oled, pillow). System: `libportaudio2` for PortAudio.

GitHub: `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio`

## User workflow (Cursor / Agent)

- Prefer **not** asking the user to copy-paste shell commands into an external terminal.
- When testing or running demos, the **coding agent should propose the exact terminal command** so the user can approve with **Run** / **OK** on the prompt.

## Commands to run (propose these for OK)

**Line-in level meter (terminal VU — stays on; Ctrl+C to stop)** — use this to confirm audio is reaching Python/PortAudio before trusting the OLED:

```bash
/home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/.venv/bin/python /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/linein_level_monitor.py
```

Optional short sanity (~3 s) if you only want to see it start and print levels:

```bash
timeout 3s /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/.venv/bin/python /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/linein_level_monitor.py
```

**One-minute terminal calibration** (then exits — enough time to start playback on the source):

```bash
timeout 60s /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/.venv/bin/python /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/linein_level_monitor.py
```

